	<quiz>
		<question>
			<para>
				<b>Question</b> What is the <latex>5</latex>-tuple whose first coordinate is <latex>1</latex>, whose second coordinate is <latex>3</latex>, whose third coordinate is <latex>-2</latex>, whose fourth coordinate is <latex>5</latex>, and whose fifth coordinate is <latex>0</latex>?</para>
		</question>
		<choice>
			<answer>
				<para>
					<latex>(1,3,2,5,0)</latex>
				</para>
			</answer>
			<info>
				<para>Correct!</para>
			</info>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<answer>
				<para>
					<latex>(3,1,2,0,5)</latex>
				</para>
			</answer>
			<info>
				<para>No! - You are using the correct numbers, but not in the correct positions. The first coordinate is the first number from the left in the tuple. So this number must be a ‘1’.</para>
			</info>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<answer>
				<para>
					<latex>(5,0,2,1,3)</latex>
				</para>
			</answer>
			<info>
				<para>No! - You are using the correct numbers, but in reverse order.</para>
			</info>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<answer>
				<para>
					<latex>(1,3,2,5)</latex>
				</para>
			</answer>
			<info>
				<para>No! - You are missing one coordinate.</para>
			</info>
		</choice>
		<choice>
			<answer>
				<para>
					<latex>(3,3,3,9,1)</latex>
				</para>
			</answer>
			<info>
				<para>No! - You need to review the definition of an <latex>n</latex>-tuple.</para>
			</info>
		</choice>
	</quiz>
	
	
	
	<quiz>
		<question>
			<para>In each of the situations below, which is the specified coordinate?</para>
		</question>
		<part>
			<question>
				<para>Third coordinate of <latex>(3,1,2,1,3)</latex></para>
			</question>
			<choice>
				<answer><para>2</para></answer>
				<info>
					<para>Correct!</para>
				</info>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<answer><para><latex>1</latex></para></answer>
				<info><para>No! - The number <latex>1</latex> appears as the value of the second and the fourth coordinate, not as the third.</para></info>
			</choice>
		</part>

		<part>
			<question><para>Second coordinate of <latex>(u,y,x,z,)</latex>?</para></question>
			<choice>
				<answer><para><latex>y</latex></para></answer>
				<info>
					<para>Correct!</para>
				</info>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<answer><para><latex>z</latex></para></answer>
				<info><para>No! - <latex>z</latex> appears in the fourth coordinate, not in the second.</para></info>
			</choice>
		</part>
